doc.after: The destruction caused by the Great Chicago Fire led to the largest building boom in the history of the nation. In 1885, the first steel-framed high-rise building, the Home Insurance Building, rose in the city as Chicago ushered in the skyscraper era,[50] which would then be followed by many other cities around the world.[100] Today, Chicago's skyline is among the world's tallest and most dense.[101]
